info.senderName: NWS Spokane (Eastern Washington and Northern Idaho)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 20 at 5:59PM PST until February 21 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Spokane
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST TUESDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph expected. * WHERE...Plummer, Genesee, Tekoa, Uniontown, Potlatch, Pullman, Rosalia, Oakesdale, Colfax, La Crosse, and Moscow. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles on north-south roads including Highway 195.
info.instruction: Remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Watch for falling debris and tree limbs. Use caution if you must drive.
